Introduction
------------
Netnotify-Client is a client for netnotify-daemon, part of netnotify project.
After connecting to netnotify-daemon it will recieve new notifications and
forward them to your local notification daemon through libnotify.

Requirements
------------
 - glib-2.0
 - gio-2.0
 - libnotify
You will also need autotools installed if you got netnotify-daemon from git
repository.

Installation
------------
Netnotify-Client uses autotools, if you got it from git repository, you would
need to run autogen.sh to prepare configure script, after that the installation
procedure is standard:
 $ ./configure
 $ make
 $ sudo make install

Usage
-----
Once itstalled netnotify-client can be started with netnotify-daemon's address
and port as arguments.

netnotify-client <host> <port>
